column5: MMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMM.......I didn't get the call???  I woulda traded you for fresh whitie fillets
The phone just rang and rang
Oh, I must have been fishing
Great goin' on the whities Bubba!!!  There must've been a few hundred hangin' around the hole for y'all to catch that many eh!!!
I know a place Terry... 14" of ice....  Great stuff Sinker !!! You're making Terry hungry ! lol
We were marking quite a few, they just didn't want to play for some reason. I think this up and down weather has them all messed up!!!  Still nice tryin!!  Sinker

I would love to hit the whities up there Wayne. I hear the fishing for them there is killer!!! Its a bit far though......considering I have more lakes here than I can fish in a lifetime with whities in them
Yah.. but a nice Northern Scenery isn't hard to handle from time to time.. LOL
NOICE.  Had some whitie fillets over the holidays and let me tell ya, the fish was delish!  Report to follow..  HD
just relax Terry ill show you how its done real soon lol if i recall i showed you last year too lol
....Mmmmm, Mmmmmm, Mmmmmmmmmmm.....whities.
Beauty fish, eh!

Hey,  I managed to get out on some ice on Monday morning at a secret whitie lake, where its open all year. We had a great day out there. Between 3 of us, we had 5 whities and 5 lakers......the lakers went back down the hole until Jan. 1st, but the whities got an invite back home for dinner ;D  This is the only pic I took, and I caught one more after this pic.    Next up is simcoe perch, and bog eyes ;D  Sinker
Great report and pic Sinker  Sounds like fun... congratulations on those nice whities Good job and thanks for sharing Leechman
That ice doesn't look that thick.
Meant to ask how thick was it?
There was about 6" of good hard clear ice, and another inch of frozen slush on top. Plenty safe for walking. There were guys out with bikes and huts too....  Sinker
WTG.  Looks like a nice simple and effective setup.

THATS WHAT ITS ABOUT RIGHT THERE!!!!!   Awesome stuff Sinker....i'm only gonna be jealous of you for 2 more days hopefully!   Cant wait for Laker opener...then i'll hit an awesome laker and whitefish lake i know.   Thanks for posting.   Simon
The laker opener for me, is walleye opener......so, yes, I've been VERY jealous of your reports up till now!!!! I'll take my revenge on the first though, so be prepared for it  Sinker
Nice work Shayne. I'm jealous as all get out.  Maybe see you on the Bog Jan 1 for eyes and crappie. And the following week in the evenings for sure.  Once again nice work!!!
Steve, I'll be at the spot. You know where it is!!! See ya out there?  Sinker
Count on it  Monday the 5th's long range weather looks prime for an evening slab fest!!!!  BTW does "THE SPOT" have a morning bite too...or just the evening?
Check your PM's buddy!!
Nice whiteys man. Drop me a line when you are hitting the bog!
W W W W H  A   T?? NO CARP?
Those are the closest thing to carp that I target! I'm not sure how a carp is, fried up in fish crisp, but if they're anything like these whities were, I"ll start fishing them tomorrow!!!!  Sinker
nice I think I need to find some secret lakes myself
Nice little report...i have never caught a whitefish and i would love to sometime.  Thanks for sharing

Terry, most of the lakes in division 15 have an open all year season, with a 12 fish/person limit. If you can find the fish, they're easy to catch......usually ......LOL.......we had to work for the ones we got!  Sinker
Care to share with a fella Newf there Shane? LOL  Nice catch bud. Im stayin away from the crisp and all batters. Just going ol natural,with some lemon and tyme. Just like Nan would make.
Yer too late Brian!! They're long gone me son!!!
good stuff buddy!  Hope to see u out on simcoe this year for  the big brothers and sisters to those whities
misfish, if we can get some ice, we can get out and catch our own they taste better when you catch them yourself.....LOL
Thats ok,we had bacon wrapped scallops. Just as good.LOL
Thats for sure bud.  Hope you been working out for the climb back up.
damn that hill
